# NIKO MODE: QA TECHNICAL VALIDATION (Main Entry)

> **TL;DR:** This is the entry point for the QA semantic review process that executes *after* BUILD mode. It performs a structured review of implemented code against the original plan, catching over-engineering, incomplete implementations, and pattern violations. Required for L2+ tasks; gates `/reflect`.

## 🚀 QA MODE ACTIVATION

After completing BUILD mode, when the user types "/qa", respond:

```mermaid
graph TD
    UserQA["User Types: /qa"] --> HighPriority["⚠️ HIGH PRIORITY COMMAND"]
    HighPriority --> CurrentTask["Pause Current Task/Process"]
    CurrentTask --> LoadQA["Load QA Main Map (This File)"]
    LoadQA --> RunQA["Execute QA Validation Process"]
    RunQA --> QAResults{"QA Results"}
    
    QAResults -->|"PASS"| ResumeFlow["Resume Prior Process Flow"]
    QAResults -->|"FAIL"| FixIssues["Fix Identified Issues"]
    FixIssues --> ReRunQA["Re-run QA Validation"]
    ReRunQA --> QAResults
    
    style UserQA fill:#f8d486,stroke:#e8b84d,color:black
    style HighPriority fill:#ff0000,stroke:#cc0000,color:white,stroke-width:3px
    style LoadQA fill:#4da6ff,stroke:#0066cc,color:white
    style RunQA fill:#4da6ff,stroke:#0066cc,color:white
    style QAResults fill:#f6546a,stroke:#c30052,color:white
```

### QA Interruption Rules

1. **Immediate Precedence:** `QA` command interrupts everything.
2. **Load & Execute:** Load this map (`van-qa-main.mdc`) and its components (see below).
3. **Remediation Priority:** Fixes take priority over pending mode switches.
4. **Resume:** On PASS, resume the previous flow.

```
⚠️ QA OVERRIDE ACTIVATED
All other processes paused
QA validation checks now running...
Any issues found MUST be remediated before continuing with normal process flow
```

## 🔍 SEMANTIC REVIEW OVERVIEW

Seven-point semantic review process:

```mermaid
graph TD
    QA["QA MODE"] --> ReadPlan["Read Original Plan<br>from tasks.md"]
    ReadPlan --> SevenChecks["SEVEN-POINT SEMANTIC REVIEW"]

    SevenChecks --> KISS["1️⃣ KISS: Simplify over-engineering"]
    SevenChecks --> DRY["2️⃣ DRY: Consolidate duplicates"]
    SevenChecks --> YAGNI["3️⃣ YAGNI: Prune speculative code"]
    SevenChecks --> Complete["4️⃣ COMPLETENESS: All requirements met?"]
    SevenChecks --> Regression["5️⃣ REGRESSION: Patterns preserved?"]
    SevenChecks --> Integrity["6️⃣ INTEGRITY: Debug artifacts removed?"]
    SevenChecks --> Integration["7️⃣ INTEGRATION INSIGHT (Advisory)"]

    KISS & DRY & YAGNI & Complete & Regression & Integrity --> ApplyFixes["Apply Fixes Directly"]
    ApplyFixes --> ReTest["Re-run Tests"]
    Integration --> Advisory["Flag for Operator"]
    ReTest --> WriteStatus["Write .qa_validation_status"]

    WriteStatus --> QAResult{"QA Result"}
    QAResult -->|"PASS"| AllowReflect["Allow /reflect"]
    QAResult -->|"FAIL"| ReturnBuild["Return to /build"]

    style QA fill:#4da6ff,stroke:#0066cc,color:white
    style SevenChecks fill:#f6546a,stroke:#c30052,color:white
    style QAResult fill:#f6546a,stroke:#c30052,color:white
    style AllowReflect fill:#10b981,stroke:#059669,color:white
    style ReturnBuild fill:#ff5555,stroke:#dd3333,color:white
```

## 📋 COMPONENT LOADING SEQUENCE

The QA process uses these utilities as needed:

1. **Main Entry (This File)**: `van-qa-main.mdc`
2. **Utilities (As Needed)**:
   - `van-qa-utils/reports.mdc` — Report generation
   - `van-qa-utils/common-fixes.mdc` — Common fix patterns
   - `van-qa-utils/mode-transitions.mdc` — Mode transition logic

## 📋 FINAL QA CHECKPOINT

```
✓ SECTION CHECKPOINT: QA SEMANTIC REVIEW
- KISS: Over-engineering addressed? [YES/NO]
- DRY: Duplicates consolidated? [YES/NO]
- YAGNI: Speculative code pruned? [YES/NO]
- COMPLETENESS: All requirements met? [YES/NO]
- REGRESSION: Patterns preserved? [YES/NO]
- INTEGRITY: Debug artifacts removed? [YES/NO]

→ If all YES: Write PASS to .qa_validation_status, proceed to /reflect.
→ If any NO: Fix issues and re-run /qa.
```

**Next Step (on PASS):** Proceed to `/reflect` (load `van-qa-utils/mode-transitions.mdc`).
**Next Step (on FAIL):** Address issues (load `van-qa-utils/common-fixes.mdc`) and re-run `/qa`. 
